item.description:
@bibbobbib wrote:

Dude I had this problem
2 ways to fix it

  1. Go to your c:// drive and find the cache. There should be another folder in there as the one you just opened. Cut and paste it into the c drive and then delete the original. You need to make sure it has the same name.
  2. Re-zip your cache. Instead of right-clicking the folder and clicking add to achieve. Highlight all the files and folders inside the cache and then right click, archieve.
    Then re-upload to your file host. Make sure you update the link to it in the CacheDownloader.java

If neither of those work idk
